Takayasu arteritis: a French single centre experience. Takayasu arteritis (TA) is an uncommon large-vessel arteritis. We report our French single-center experience in the management of patients with TA (Pitié-Salpêtrière Hospital, Paris). TA is diagnosed in patients presenting with a large-vessel arteriopathy, in whom several inflammatory and non-inflammatory differential diagnoses are ruled out by appropriate investigations. Treatment of active disease is primarily based on corticosteroids but other immunosuppressive drugs are frequently needed. Anti-platelets agents, statins and antihypertensive drugs are frequently considered. There is no validated disease activity criterion in TA thus, we generally consider the disease as being active in the presence of the following criteria: firstly, the presence of constitutional or ischemic symptoms